data.description: Exceptional single-story, creek-front family home in a quiet, secluded estate neighborhood. Backs up to Lake Georgetown - minutes to boat launch; One of only a few lots with gently sloped useable land and access to a tranquil running creek and lake trails! Private park-like setting. Corps of Engineers Property. Mature pear and apricot trees. Tons of Parking Space - circular driveway! Garage Shelving w/Sink; 3.5 Car Garage (fits 28' boat); Gated Backyard with up to 40' RV/Boat parking with 30amp and water hookup. 12' Ceilings & 20" Tile throughout.  Insulation exceeds Energy-Star; dual-pane windows; radiant barrier roofing; LED recessed can lights; programmable thermostat; all GFI circuit breaker updated for safety and to code recently; wall plates and switches updated with dimmers, motion sensors, USB, smart/wifi and/or lit wall plates; multiple plug outlets per room. Security, Satellite & Cable; Dual Attic Entry; Dual-Controlled Central AC/Heat; Dual 50 gallon water heaters;  Plumbed propane for BBQ; Several 230V outlets (EV charger/Tesla in garage);  Dog Run/Door
